The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Rupee pressure on debt 
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Rupee pressure on debt 
                            
	New Delhi, April 4 (PTI): Exchange rate fluctuation has inflated Indias external debt by $18.7 billion (about Rs 90,000 crore) during the three-month period ended December 31, 2009, according to the Reserve Bank of India.        
	If the US dollar had weakened against other currencies, including the rupee, external debt would have declined $10 billion during September-December 2009, said the report on external debt.        
	After taking into account the valuation effect of $18.7 billion  the changes in the value of assets India holds abroad minus the changes in the value of domestic assets held by foreign investors  external debt during the three-month period rose $8.7 billion to $251.4 billion.         
	In rupee terms, the debt worked out to about Rs 12 lakh crore.        
	At the end of December, the external debt basket comprised 52 per cent of dollar-denominated debt.                                                                                                                                       
